Nearly 300km through forest along the foot-hills of The Great Dividing Range. No where in the 300km is the road either straight or level or without potholes patched and unpatched. The one exception was the first few 'k' into Victoria. Magnificent road. "Ah we thought" Victoria knows how to do it, but the road so deteriorated back to NSW country road standard.
